     Given the constraints, Redis Streams is the better fit. The team lacks Kafka expertise and would face a steep learning curve with significant operational overhead. Redis Streams leverages their existing infrastructure, can[0m[2m handle the 10x growth requirement, and provides the ordering and delivery guarantees needed for billing notifications. The lower operational complexity and faster migration timeline align with their constraints, though I'll need to implement idempotency handling for exactly-once semantics[0m[2m on the consumer side.
     
